    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Terracotta oil lamps having a spout for the wick, an enclosed area  for the oil, and often a handle. The term refers literally to ancient Greek lamps of this design, but may be applied to such lamps from any period or region.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047708/Christie's Online (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種赤陶油燈，具支撐燈芯之燈嘴、盛裝燈油之封閉空間、通常還有握把。一般用以指稱具此造型之古希臘油燈，但也可指任何時期或地區之同類型燈具。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Öllampe aus Terrakotta mit einer Tülle für den Docht, einem umschlossenen Ölreservoir und häufig einem Griff. Der Begriff bezieht sich eigentlich auf antike griechische Lampen dieser Bauart, kann aber auch für ähnliche Lampen aus jedem Zeitalter oder Land gebraucht werden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
